properties.Title: Update: High Water Advisory Alert Is Being Issued For The Roseau River From Gardenton To Stuartburn
properties.Summary:
Description: Update: This is a Manitoba Emergency Alert. Manitoba Infrastructure's Hydrologic Forecast Centre has issued a High Water Advisory for the Roseau River from Gardenton to Stuartburn due to expected high flows. If you are in the affected area, be watchful of local waterways as flooding is likely to occur. Do not attempt to cross fast flowing waters or waters of unknown depth. Avoid flooded areas. Follow all directions by the local authorities. Listen for updates and take all necessary precautions to stay safe. Up-to-date information is available at www.gov.mb.ca/flooding and www.manitoba511.ca or stay tuned to local media.
Expires: 2019-11-22T16:00:00-06:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Manitoba Emergency Measures Organization, 2019-11-21T15:49:23-06:00, 6BD8BB9A-F4CB-D70C-6472-CFBF3F107AB3
Area: Roseau River from Gardenton to Stuartburn
properties.Author: Manitoba Emergency Measures Organization

properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Strong wind gusts tonight. Strong southwesterly wind gusts up to 80 km/h are possible beginning this evening. The strong winds will begin to ease overnight tonight. Be prepared to adjust your driving with changing road conditions due to high winds. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. properties.Title: Snowfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Snowfall with total amounts of 15 to 20 cm is expected. Snow at times heavy is expected over the Highlands of Inverness County on Saturday, starting in the morning and persisting into Saturday night. Accumulations of up to 25 centimetres are expected. Wet snow is expected over lower elevations of Inverness County. However, accumulations are expected to be much lower, in the 5 to 10 centimetre range, due to the fact that temperatures are forecast to remain slightly above freezing. ### Rapidly accumulating snow could make travel difficult over some locations. Visibility may be suddenly reduced at times in heavy snow. Snowfall warnings are issued when significant snowfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NSstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NSStorm.
Expires: 2019-11-23T01:24:58-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2019-11-22T09:25:58-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.1303765591.2019
Area: Inverness County - Mabou and north

properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Blizzard conditions with poor visibility in snow and blowing snow are expected or occurring. An approaching weather system will bring strong winds producing blizzard conditions to Ulukhaktok later this morning. Conditions are forecast to improve on Saturday. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Blizzard warnings are issued when widespread reduced visibilities of 400 metres or less are expected for at least 6 hours. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NTStorm.
Expires: 2019-11-23T03:59:59-00:00
